A '''Berman hearing''' is a provision under [[California]] law for the administrative resolution of [[wage]] claims under the California Labor Commissioner in accordance with the provisions of the California Labor Code, §98.  The hearing is named after [[Howard Berman]], the member of the California State Assembly who instituted it.<ref>''Post v. Palo/Haklar & Associates'' 98 Cal.Rptr.2d 671, 674 (2000)</ref>

