{{Citation style|date=February 2016}} '''Ibn Fahd Helli''' ({{lang-fa|ابن فهد حلی}}) was an eminent [[Ja'fari jurisprudence|Shia jurist]] and religious scientist in the eighth and ninth [[Hijri year|Hijrah lunar]].
==Early life== He lived for a while in [[Hilla]] in [[Iraq]]. [[Hilla]] was one of the first center of Shi'a scholars such as ibn Fahd.<ref name="Momen2015">{{cite book|last=Momen|first=Moojan|authorlink= Moojan Momen|title=Shi'I Islam: A Beginner's Guide|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7WS1CgAAQBAJ&pg=PT59|date=11 May 2015|publisher=Oneworld Publications|isbn=978-1-78074-788-0|page=59}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cgie.org.ir/fa/publication/entryview/2708|title=دائرة المعارف بزرگ اسلامی:ابن فهد حلی|website=Cgie.org.ir|accessdate=2016-02-28}}</ref> He began his education in Zaynabiyyah school. He may have also lived briefly in [[Karbala]].<ref>{{Harvnb|Khansari| Rawdat al-Jannat| vol= 1|pp=71–72}}</ref>{{full citation needed|date=February 2016}}
==Scientific activity== His life is coincided with a [[Mongols|Mongol]] attack, but he was safe from this catastrophe since he lived during the [[Jalairid Sultanate|Jalayeri sultanate]] . He had teachers such as Fazil Meghdad, Hasan ibn Hasan Al Deylami, Shaykh Ahmad Motavvaj Bahrani, Baha Al Ddin Nassabeh, Sayyed jamal Aaraj Hoseini, Shaykh Ahmad ibn Motavvej Bahrani.<ref>{{harv|Modarres Tabrizi|vol=8|p=193|Reyhant Al Adab}}</ref>{{full citation needed|date=February 2016}}Also He taught pupils [[Fiqh|Islamic Jurisprudence]] (Fiqh), mysticism and traditions like Ibn Tay, ibn Asharah and Ali ibn Helal Jazaeri.<ref>{{harv|Aqa Bozorg Tehrani| Tabaghat Aalam Shia|vol=4}}</ref>{{full citation needed|date=February 2016}}
==Works== He wrote books on different aspects of Islamic sciences such as [[Islamic mysticism|mysticism]], [[Islamic jurisprudence|jurisprudence]], [[Islamic tradition|tradition]] and other religious spheres. Some of them are: * ''Al Awiyah va Al Fatum'' * ''Istekhraj Al Havadeth'' (predicting some events, such as appearance of Safavid dynasty and Mongol's Attack by Ali ibn Abi Talib * ''The Mysteries of Praying'' * ''Tahsin fi Sefat al Arefin''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lib.eshia.ir/15042/1/4 |title=کتابخانه مدرسه فقاهت - التحصين - ابن فهد الحلي |website=Lib.eshia.ir |date= |accessdate=2016-02-28}}</ref> * ''Iddat Al Daei''
==Death== He died at age 84 and was buried in [[Karbala]].<ref>{{Harvnb|Khansari| Rawdat al-Jannat| vol= 1|p=74}}</ref>{{full citation needed|date=February 2016}}
